      "name": "Hemolysis index validation against FDA GCBP bench data (Q1 2026)",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) compared against FDA generic centrifugal blood pump experimental measurements across 5 operating points. Mean absolute error in RHI was 4.2%, within the acceptance threshold of 10%. The validation was executed using solver configuration ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which was the release candidate active at the time of the validation campaign. The released production build (ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7) differs only at the rc2 suffix level, reflecting a single patch-level increment. The responsible engineer documented that the two builds are effectively the same solver executable, with the rc2-to-release transition involving only documentation updates and a minor installer fix with no changes to the numerical kernel. On this basis, the validation results generated under the rc2 configuration were carried forward without re-execution under the released build.",
